    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Presenting a driver-focused 996-generation Carrera, powered by a 3.4L naturally aspirated flat-six paired with a precise 6-speed G96 manual transaxle. This example features a documented IMS bearing retrofit and a recently replaced rear main seal, ensuring mechanical longevity. The suspension retains its factory-intended poise, utilizing a MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear configuration that provides exceptional turn-in and communicative feedback through the hydraulic steering rack. The engine exhibits strong compression and linear power delivery across the rev range, complemented by a stainless steel exhaust that highlights the boxer's distinct acoustic signature. The chassis is rigid, and the braking system utilizes four-piston monobloc calipers for consistent thermal management and stopping power. This is a mechanically sound, high-performance machine ready for the enthusiast who values driving dynamics over concours perfection.",
